tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE survey_responses (
    response_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    survey_id INT,
    user_id INT,
    response_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    demographic_category VARCHAR,
    completion_time_minutes INT
);

CREATE TABLE survey_responses (
    response_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT NOT NULL,
    question_id INT NOT NULL,
    response_value TEXT,
    response_timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE demographic_info (
    user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    age INT,
    gender TEXT,
    location TEXT,
    income DECIMAL
);
CREATE TABLE SurveyResponses (id INT, user_id INT, demographics VARCHAR, response_time INT);
CREATE TABLE Demographics (id INT, user_id INT, age INT, gender VARCHAR, location VARCHAR);
CREATE TABLE SurveyCompletionTimes (id INT, user_id INT, survey_id INT, completion_time INT);

CREATE TABLE survey_responses (
    response_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    survey_id INT,
    respondent_id INT,
    response_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    response_text VARCHAR(255)
);

CREATE TABLE survey_completion_times (
    survey_id INT,
    respondent_id INT,
    completion_time_min INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (survey_id) REFERENCES survey_responses(survey_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (respondent_id) REFERENCES respondent_demographics(respondent_id)
);

CREATE TABLE survey_responses (
 response_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 survey_id INT,
 user_id INT,
 response_text TEXT,
 response_time TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE survey_demographics (
 survey_id INT,
 user_id INT,
 age INT,
 gender VARCHAR(10),
 location VARCHAR(50),
 completion_time INTERVAL
);
